============================================================
PHASE 20 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the self-evolving enterprise operating system layer for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Add Enterprise OS capability map
2. Add enterprise operating cadence engine
3. Add safe self-improvement proposal system
4. Add architecture drift detector
5. Add technical debt and quality intelligence engine
6. Add test coverage and reliability improvement advisor
7. Add schema/API evolution proposal workflow
8. Add safe change proposal generator
9. Add autonomous governance refinement engine
10. Add policy maturity scoring
11. Add governance drift detection
12. Add policy simulation and control impact analysis
13. Add risk appetite and control calibration model
14. Add lessons-learned memory system
15. Add long-horizon strategy intelligence engine
16. Add trend radar and horizon scanning system
17. Add strategic thesis tracker
18. Add moat / advantage / defensibility analysis shell
19. Add 3-year / 5-year / 10-year scenario planning system
20. Add Enterprise OS frontend pages, tests, docs, runbooks, and final acceptance gates

IMPORTANT SAFETY RULES:
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- Do not bypass billing entitlements.
- Do not bypass governance policies.
- Do not bypass final GA safety gates.
- Do not bypass data residency enforcement.
- Do not allow self-modifying production code.
- Do not auto-commit, auto-merge, auto-deploy, auto-migrate, auto-scale, auto-delete, or auto-change infrastructure.
- Self-evolution means proposal generation only.
- All improvement proposals require human review, approval, CI validation, security review, and rollback plan.
- Governance refinement must never weaken safety controls automatically.
- Long-horizon strategy outputs are advisory planning estimates, not guarantees.
- Legal/compliance outputs are templates only, not legal advice.
- Capital/resource allocation simulations are planning-only, not financial advice.
- No automated outreach, pricing changes, billing changes, trading actions, hiring/firing actions, legal actions, or public announcements may run automatically.
- No secrets, credentials, tokens, broker credentials, private customer payloads, raw prompts, API keys, KMS refs, runner tokens, cloud credentials, or confidential documents may be logged, exported, synced, or displayed.
- Every proposal, simulation, and recommendation must include assumptions, confidence, evidence summary, limitations, risks, and rollback considerations.

