IMPORTANT IMPLEMENTATION RULES
============================================================

- Do not use pseudocode.
- Do not skip files.
- Do not remove Phase 1–19 behavior.
- Keep all existing backend tests passing.
- Keep all existing frontend tests passing.
- Keep mobile tests passing.
- Keep desktop tests passing.
- Keep SDK tests passing.
- Use typed Python where reasonable.
- Use TypeScript types.
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style.
- Never hardcode secrets.
- Never expose secrets in frontend, mobile, desktop, SDKs, reports, proposals, lessons, logs, docs, or exports.
- Never log API keys, KMS key refs, runner tokens, broker credentials, cloud credentials, private payloads, or confidential sources.
- Never store raw confidential sources by default.
- Never enable live trading by default.
- Never enable real social posting by default.
- Never enable real IoT power actions by default.
- Never bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Never bypass content approval checks.
- Never bypass tenant isolation.
- Never bypass billing entitlements.
- Never bypass governance policies.
- Never bypass final GA safety gates.
- Never bypass data residency enforcement.
- Never allow self-evolution to modify code, schemas, infrastructure, policies, routes, tests, or runtime behavior directly.
- Never auto-commit, auto-merge, auto-deploy, auto-migrate, or auto-delete.
- Never weaken safety policies automatically.
- Never present long-horizon strategy as guaranteed.
- Never present legal/compliance templates as legal advice.
- Never present capital/resource allocation as financial advice.
- Keep all proposals advisory, evidence-linked, confidence-scored, rollback-planned, and approval-gated.
